title: A year after Mahsa Amini’s death: Repression and defiance in Iran
description: The last year gave the world a glimpse of the seething anger just below the surface of Iran’s repressive society. But it also highlighted the resilience of the regime.

title: Quake tourism slump could cut lifeline to Morocco’s mountain villages
description: In the aftermath of an earthquake in Morocco, many who rely on tourism, an industry already beleaguered by the coronavirus epidemic, fear for their livelihoods.

title: Princess Diana’s ‘black sheep’ sweater breaks auction records
description: Princess Diana’s black sheep sweater, made by Warm and Wonderful and worn in 1981, is now “the most valuable sweater ever sold at auction,” Sotheby’s said.

title: Fernando Botero, Colombian artist of rotund and whimsical imagery, dies at 91
description: His emblematic oversized figures, evoking vanity, pomposity and greed, brought global attention to Latin American art.

title: The hunt for wild crocodile eggs that feeds the designer handbag craze
description: Luxury brands use crocodile leather for their pricey products. For Indigenous Australians, that creates an opportunity.

title: What is Nipah virus? India rushes to contain outbreak.
description: The virus has killed two so far and infected at least five in the state of Kerala and is considered a priority disease by the WHO for its epidemic potential.

title: Their loved ones were killed in Iran’s uprising. Then the state came for them.
description: A year after Mahsa Amini’s death, family members of protesters killed in Iran have been systematically surveilled and detained by the authorities.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Zelensky headed to Washington; Kim Jong Un visits jet factory in Russia
description: President Volodymyr Zelensky seeks to persuade U.S. lawmakers to green-light a $24 billion assistance package for Ukraine. Kim Jong Un continues his Russia trip.

title: Argentina takes down ‘prolific’ clandestine Nazi printing press
description: Argentina’s Federal Police raided a man’s home Tuesday, conducting the country’s largest seizure of materials espousing Nazi propaganda in recent years.

title: Shuffle of Russian military chiefs preceded death of Wagner boss Prigozhin
description: Before the plane crash that killed mercenary boss Yevgeniy Prigozhin, a consolidation of military leaders running Vladimir Putin’s war in Ukraine was already underway.

title: China’s defense minister under investigation for corruption
description: The expected purge of Li Shangfu comes after the foreign minister and two top military leaders were sacked, heightening concerns about how China’s foreign policy is being managed.

title: Libya’s catastrophe is everyone’s fault
description: Libya’s two regimes left critical infrastructure in a state of neglect. But the intervention of myriad outside powers laid the groundwork for disaster.
